article.description: Danielle Adams scored 22 points and Texas A&M (No. 8 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) shot 53 percent in a 79-59 win over Auburn on Sunday.
article.headline: No. 8 Texas A&M's defense forces 23 turnovers to beat Auburn
article.linkText: Texas A&M limits Auburn to 38 percent shooting
article.story:
AUBURN, Ala. -- Danielle Adams scored 22 points and Texas A&M (No. 8 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) shot 53 percent from the field in a 79-59 win over Auburn on Sunday.

The Aggies (3-0) played stifling defense against the Tigers (2-2), holding the defending Southeastern Conference champions to 38 percent shooting and forcing 23 turnovers.

Tanisha Smith had 14 points, four assists and six of Texas A&M's 15 steals. Adaora Elonu added 13 points on 6-of-8 shooting.

Alli Smalley led Auburn with 18 points, but also committed six turnovers. Keke Carrier added nine points and eight rebounds.

Texas A&M led 36-26 at halftime. Smalley scored the first two points of the second half on a pair of free throws, but the Tigers couldn't come any closer.

Elonu and Adams both made a layup and a free throw to push the lead back to 14 points. Texas A&M made 17-of-30 shots in the second half.
